Research Guides

Created by our subject librarians, Research Guides explore resources related to a specific subject, topic, course, or type of source.

Research Support

Digital Humanities

Digital Humanities is a framework of digital tools and methodologies for studying the humanities and advancing humanities scholarship.

PEN & Inc.

Learn more about our digital project incubator program for new digitally inflected projects and an active-participant incubator/mentorship program to assist projects in their development.

Grant Programs

FSU Libraries offers grant to support varied work in teaching, research, and publishing.

GEOSET

GEOSET offers media production and training to the FSU community as one among many digital media library resources.

CreateFSU Web Hosting

CreateFSU is a free, web hosting service for members of the Florida State University Community.

Research Data Services

FSU Libraries provide research data services to support and collaborate with scholars in areas related to data analysis & visualization, digital humanities, GIS, and research data management.

Open Access @ FSU

Open Access Support

We aim to provide open access publishing expertise, services, and platforms to enhance the scholarly output of Florida State University students, faculty, and staff.

Open Access Publishing Fund

Florida State Open Publishing provides faculty, students and staff with the digital publishing tools and support needed to produce peer-reviewed, open scholarly publications, educational resources, and other digital research outputs.

Open Scholars Project

The Open Scholars Project is an informal forum to learn about and discuss developments in open access.

Other Services

Immersive Scholarship

Immersive Scholarship focuses on developing and expanding support for virtual reality, augmented reality, 3D scanning, and 3D printing services.

Demos Project

The Demos Project at FSU fosters and supports scholarship involving structured data around people and their environment.

Copyright Support

Learn more about copyright, fair use, and the support offered for navigating copyright in the Libraries.
